### React Testing Library

React Testing Library (RTL) provides light utility functions on top of react-dom and react-dom/test-utils. It encourages testing components from the user's perspective.

---

### Core Methods

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `render(ui)` | Renders component into a DOM container |
| `screen.getByText()` | Finds element by visible text |
| `screen.getByRole()` | Finds element by ARIA role |
| `screen.getByLabelText()` | Finds input by associated label |
| `screen.getByTestId()` | Finds element by data-testid |
| `screen.queryByText()` | Returns null if not found (no error) |
| `screen.findByText()` | Returns promise (for async elements) |

### Query Priority

1. Accessible by everyone: `getByRole`, `getByLabelText`, `getByPlaceholderText`
2. Semantic queries: `getByText`, `getByDisplayValue`
3. Test IDs: `getByTestId` (last resort)

### User Events

```jsx
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';

const user = userEvent.setup();

await user.type(input, 'Hello');
await user.click(button);
await user.selectOptions(select, ['option1']);
await user.clear(input);
await user.keyboard('{Enter}');
// Prefer userEvent over fireEvent for realistic interactions
```

### Async Testing

```jsx
import { render, screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';

it('loads data', async () => {
  render(<UserProfile userId={1} />);

  expect(screen.getByText(/loading/i)).toBeInTheDocument();

  const name = await screen.findByText('Alice');
  expect(name).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

> **Key Point:** Always query elements the way users find them: by role, label, or visible text. Avoid test IDs unless there is no accessible way. Use userEvent instead of fireEvent for realistic interactions.

codeExample:
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';

import SearchBar from './SearchBar';

describe('SearchBar', () => {
  it('updates search value on type', async () => {
    const user = userEvent.setup();
    render(<SearchBar onSearch={() => {}} />);

    const input = screen.getByRole('textbox');
    await user.type(input, 'react');

    expect(input).toHaveValue('react');
  });

  it('shows suggestions when focused', async () => {
    render(<SearchBar onSearch={() => {}} />);
    const input = screen.getByRole('textbox');
    await userEvent.click(input);
    expect(screen.getByText(/recent searches/i)).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
